I'm a PhD candidate in Public Administration and Government at <a href="https://eaesp.fgv.br/" target="_blank">Fundação Getulio Vargas (EAESP FGV)</a>, graduate research assistant at <a href="https://ieps.org.br/" target="_blank">IEPS-SP</a>, and founder at LAPP (Public Policy and Social Programs Lab), a platform that seeks to gather, organize and provide straightforward information (causal evidence) on the impacts of public policy and social programs that went under rigorous evaluation worldwide. I also hold a bachelor's degree from the <a href="https://eesp.fgv.br/en" target="_blank">São Paulo School of Economics (EESP/FGV)</a> and a master's degree from <a href="https://www.tilburguniversity.edu/" target="_blank">Tilburg University</a>, all in economics. I truly believe that evidence-informed decision-making is the key to the development and strengthening of public policies and to positively impact the livelihoods of those who need the most.

\

**Research Interests**: policy impact evaluation, health and demographic economics, public health

**Email**: mszklo@gmail.com

